i## GPS Module Installation and Configuration		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFirst, connect the GPS module's serial port. The ATGM336H operates at		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3.3V, so it can connect directly to Tinker Board:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Module VCC → Pin 17 (3.3V power)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Module GND → Pin 20 (ground)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Module RX → Pin 8 (UART1 TX)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Module TX → Pin 10 (UART1 RX)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Module PPS → Pin 22		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iLog into Tinker Board (I used Armbian OS). Run `armbian-config` ,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ienable all `uart` options under **System > Hardware** , then reboot.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iInstall gpsd to process GPS data:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  apt-get install gpsd gpsd-clients		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iEdit `/etc/default/gpsd` with these settings:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  START_DAEMON="true"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  USBAUTO="false"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  DEVICES="/dev/ttyS1"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  GPSD_OPTIONS="-n -b"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThis enables gpsd, specifies the serial port ( `ttyS1` ), starts		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ipositioning immediately, and prevents configuration changes.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iStart gpsd:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  systemctl enable gpsd		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  systemctl start gpsd		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iRun `cgps` to view location and satellite status:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
